    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/8–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-01T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 1, 1951—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>660. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 578 July 28 to Dept rptd New Delhi
                    18 Karachi 18.</p>
                <p>1. Emb Off has seen replies from <gloss target="#t_UKHC1">UKHC</gloss>’s New
                    Delhi and Karachi describing reaction Zafrullah and Bajpai to representations
                    briefly outlined Reftel. Both Zafrullah and Bajpai made polite but somewhat
                    equivocal remarks general tenor of which was their own positions unassailable
                    and concessions shld be made by other side.</p>
                <p>2. New Delhi, Garner reported he suggested as on own personal initiative <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> observers might be sent Punjab frontier. Bajpai
                    reported to have replied this an entirely new suggestion and <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> had not considered such a possibility. He
                    promised think it over.</p>
                <p>3. In response to similar approach at Karachi Zafrullah said his govt had thought
                    of this possibility but was reluctant at present <pb facs="0341" n="1805"
                        xml:id="pg_1805"/> stage ask <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> take any kind
                    of action, although Pakistan might later appeal to <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> if situation did not improve.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 660 rptd info New Delhi 21 Karachi 21.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
